 # CHANGELOG
 
+## 2026-07-18
+
+### Application Stabilization
+
+Fixed:
+
+- Start Duty now uses only field-duty sessions, rejects already-completed attendance days, verifies the first GPS/Firestore update, and surfaces the underlying failure message.
+- Map mode selection and action panels are isolated by user role; Administrator users no longer receive Service Engineer duty or visit controls.
+- Cab-management permissions now derive from the user role instead of unconditional `true` values, and non-manager users can no longer inherit an unrelated manager assignment.
+- Full-map refreshes no longer replace the GoogleMap with a loading state; realtime refreshes are debounced and prevented from overlapping.
+- Live-location writes are serialized to prevent out-of-order history sequence updates and duplicate concurrent writes.
+- Realtime listeners are scoped to the active mode and, where possible, the signed-in user or current date.
+- Shared dark theme coverage now includes Material color scheme, cards, dividers, inputs, dialogs, popup menus, bottom sheets, snackbars, navigation, and floating actions.
+- Administrator Map KPI tiles now respond to available width and use consistent monochrome styling.
+
+Preserved:
+
+- Existing navigation, controllers, services, models, Firestore collection names, and business workflows.
+- No new business module or architecture was introduced.
+
+Validation:
+
+- `git diff --check`: passed.
+- `flutter clean`: passed.
+- `flutter pub get`: passed with the existing locked dependency versions.
+- `flutter analyze`: no issues found.
+- `flutter test`: all 16 tests passed.
+
 ## 2026-07-12
 
 ### Map UI Foundation Complete
