 # PROJECT STATUS
 
+## 2026-07-18 - Stabilization Sprint
+
+Completed:
+
+- Isolated Map modes by signed-in role so Administrator, Driver, Employee, and Service Engineer users only receive their permitted controls.
+- Removed the unsafe cab-management defaults that granted every role manager capabilities and exposed the first manager assignment to unassigned users.
+- Fixed Start Duty session selection so field duty cannot reuse cab-trip or pickup location sessions.
+- Made Start Duty wait for an actual GPS fix and successful first live-location/history writes before reporting success.
+- Prevented a completed attendance record from being silently reused as a successful new check-in.
+- Preserved the GoogleMap during refreshes, debounced realtime changes, blocked overlapping refreshes, narrowed mode listeners, and serialized live-location writes.
+- Completed the shared dark Nothing OS theme for cards, fields, dialogs, menus, sheets, snackbars, dividers, navigation, and floating actions.
+- Made Map KPI tiles responsive and standardized administrator map surfaces, status colors, spacing, and contrast.
+- Audited timers, animation controllers, text controllers, subscriptions, mounted checks, and disposal paths in the current application.
+
+Validation status:
+
+- Repository whitespace/patch validation passes with `git diff --check`.
+- `flutter clean` and `flutter pub get` pass with the existing locked dependency versions.
+- `flutter analyze` reports no issues.
+- `flutter test` passes all 16 tests.
+
+Remaining production blockers:
+
+- Firestore security rules are not present in this repository or referenced by `firebase.json`.
+- Google Maps rendering still depends on valid Google Cloud billing, enabled Maps SDKs, API-key restrictions, and device verification.
+- Background location, device battery optimization behavior, and platform permission flows require physical-device validation.
+- Global offline/retry UX is not uniformly implemented; adding it is a separate production feature and was outside this no-new-features sprint.
+
